Step 1. Compute Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• Given Gross Profit = 2,272,433.90 and Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90,
  Gross Profit Margin = (2,272,433.90 / 3,956,433.90) × 100% ≈ 57.48%

Step 2. Compute Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities)
• Given Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1,182,491.05 and Total Current Liabilities = 499,821.72,
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -1,182,491.05 / 499,821.72 ≈ -2.37

Thus, the answer is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "57.48%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-2.37"
  }
}
